# Who reviews what.
#
# GitHub assigns reviewers automatically from the paths a PR touches. The rules
# mirror the lane table in AGENTS.md — the same boundaries the parallel agents
# work inside, enforced at review time instead of by convention.
#
# Last match wins, so the shared-foundation block at the bottom overrides the
# lane rules above it: a PR touching both a lane and src/lib/ still needs the
# foundation owner.
#
# Everything points at @CaBsCrypto today. As people join, swap the owner on the
# lane they take over — that is the only edit needed.

# Default owner for anything not matched below
*                           @CaBsCrypto

